its not that its 1 file   its that for most systems, our archivers will crash or run into error frequently due to the file size (takes forever for my system to read the archive and i have a quad core), spliting it into rars for each folder would have been more optimized

We all need to learn by our mistakes. If I ever release another one, it'll be split into sections. As for the winrar crashing, that's never happened to me. It's also fairly easier to locate when it's all in one file. It's made to be extracted and then the rar either seeded or deleted.
Optimization isn't really going to be that much better split or not.
But, as I said, I will split it next time.
